His favorite ice cream flavor is either Carrot Cake from Furniture City or Lavender Blueberry from Love's Ice Cream
Fun Fact: He let Jason Cooke beat him in a foot race one time. Jason really needed a win that day.
He loves teaching at WMAAA because it gives kids with a passion for art a place to learn and grow
Ben and his wife were excited to welcome a second daughter to their family this summer. Just enough time had passed to forget the sleeping habits of newborns!

post_text: Meet the staff: Fun facts about me: I love any opportunity to be a world traveler; one of my favorite activities is camping; I love the water and the beach - if you need to find me in the summer, I am most likely at the beach or by the water; summer is my favorite season, although, fall is a very close second; music means more to me than words can describe and I attempt to instill that passion and love of music in my students; my favorite movie is ‚ÄúThe Greatest Showman‚Äù; my favorite color is Red; Why I love this school so much: WMAAA has the most encouraging, supportive, involved, and welcoming staff who love their profession and more importantly, love each and every one of our amazing students! post_text:
Meet the Staff! Ms. Boeve!!! 2 Truths and a lie:
I love to golf
I hate broccoli
My dog and I share a birthday

This is my fifth year teaching! I‚Äôve taught in first grade, preschool, fourth grade and now virtual fourth grade; I couldn‚Äôt choose which grade I like best because they‚Äôre all fun in their own ways. In my free time I like to walk my dog, Murphy Lee, golf with friends, and read at the beach. I also enjoying coloring/painting, cooking and traveling! Did you guess which was the lie? My dog and I really do share a birthday! I was on the golf team in high school, and still golf today! Broccoli is actually my favorite vegetable! I‚Äôm looking forward to another amazing year at WMAAA, we simply have the best teachers, staff, students and families.
--

post_text: Meet the Staff! Miss Vlasak is our Middle School Resource Teacher. This will be her 4th year with WMAAA. Ashley enjoys hiking around our beautiful state and traveling to other destinations around the country. This photo was taken last year on a trip she took to Arizona. She loves spending time outdoors, especially with her two adorable Australian Shepherds. She also loves doing yoga, practicing her photography skills, and spending time with her family and friends. Some of her favorite things include black coffee, sunflowers, and reading on her front porch.

post_text:
Meet the Staff! Mrs. DeBoer (Theatre) and Mrs. Oster (Dance) Mrs. DeBoer is excited to be starting her 14th year at WMAAA and Mrs. Oster is excited to be starting her 4th year at WMAAA.
Fun facts, Mrs Oster has two golden retrievers named Aspen and Breck.
Mrs. DeBoer has two kiddos that attend WMAAA. Emerson in 4th grade and Oliver in kindergarten. She also has a rescue pup named Hercules Mulligan (yes, after the historical figure who is featured in the musical Hamilton).
Both Mrs. DeBoer and Mrs. Oster got to travel to NYC the summer of 2019 and take master classes and see 4 Broadway shows in 3 days! (See picture!) It was an incredible experience!
Both of us love working at WMAAA because the staff, students, and families are amazing! And because we love that WMAAA recognizes the importance of arts in education!

post_text:
Here is our amazing new Kinder teacher, Ms. Hochhuth! Here are some fun facts about Ms. H!
Being a kindergarten teacher has been a life-long dream of mine. I am so happy to be here at West Michigan Academy!

When I am not teaching in the classroom, I like to spend time hiking around our beautiful state! I love to appreciate Michigan‚Äôs dunes, beaches, and lakes. You can usually find me hiking with my dogs (I have four of them!). My favorite desserts are chocolate chip cookies and brownies (I have a big sweet tooth!). I love the arts. My favorite role I have played was Cinderella in Into The Woods - I actually played this part in two different productions. I also enjoy painting, singing, kayaking, reading, and spending time with my family!

The AMAZING ART ADVENTURE!! Complete a challenge, get a spirit stick! So Cool!

Week 3 Challenges (May 4 - 9)
Visual Arts
Rock Art
Paint a rock with a positive message (i.e. Hope, Kindness, You are not alone, etc)
Place it somewhere around your neighborhood for others to enjoy
Snap a pic and share on Facebook or Instagram and tag us @wmaaaschool

Dance
Watch Party
Watch the following dance performances - ALVIN AILEY AMERICAN DANCE THEATER (2002-03), Swan Lake, Tchaikovsky - Dance of the Little Swans, Misty Copeland Dances Romeo + Juliet, Tschaikovsky Pas de Deux & White Swan at Vail Dance 2015
Tell us which is your favorite and why
Share with us on Facebook or Instagram and tag us @wmaaaschool

Music
Make an Instrument
Create an instrument from supplies around your house.
Perform a song with your instrument.
Share with us on Facebook or Instagram and tag us @wmaaaschool

Drama
Disney Scene
Act out a favorite scene from a Disney Movie
Post your video on Facebook or Instagram and tag us @wmaaaschool

shared_text:
Detroit Symphony Orchestra
May 1 at 10:28 AM ¬∑

We're mixing things up for our weekly Educational Concert Series Watch Party starting today! Our team has begun curating all-new educational concerts from previous DSO Classical Series performances, with new Student Mini-Guides containing accompanying lessons and activities.

Join us at at 2 PM ET for "Storytelling Through Music and Dance." The program features the music of Igor Stravinsky and George Gershwin, and includes special talks with DSO violist (and ballroom dancer!) Caroline Coade and Suttle Dance - SDC Artistic Director Sylvia Suttle. Don't forget to check out the Mini-Guide with your students to get the most out of watching: https://bit.ly/2VUwDmW

April 7 at 3:03 PM ¬∑

After your student has learned about these musical terms, tune in to our Facebook Watch Party Wednesday 4/8 at 2PM ET to view our 2019 Educational Concert Series performance of ‚ÄúDvo≈ô√°k‚Äôs New World Symphony: Finding the American Voice.‚Äù Students can practice identifying musical terms while the DSO performs one of the world‚Äôs most beloved symphonies, conducted by Enrico Lopez-Ya√±ez‚Äîthey‚Äôll even learn some important American history along the way.



When learning a new word, students must ‚Äúdecode‚Äù its letter sounds to pronounce it and use context clues to decipher its meaning. Music students need similar skills when learning to read music! Music contains many different symbols, which represent volume, playing style, and more. This worksheet helps students practice their clue-finding skills while learning musical terms.

Dear Academy Families,

With a possible ‚Äúshelter in place‚Äù order imminent, we would like to provide chromebooks to families that need them. If you need a chromebook, please come to the school between 11:30am and 4:00pm or 6:00pm and 7:30pm today - March 23rd.

Please, stay in your car and we will bring the chromebook and charger to you. You will sign out the machine and bring it home. Please remember, we will need these machines back after the crisis.

We will try to get chromebooks out later if you are unable to pick one up today.

Please limit one chromebook per family.

These chromebooks currently do not have a filtering mechanism. This should be added shortly but please be aware that you will need to monitor your children‚Äôs online activities.

Stay safe, warm, and healthy over these next few weeks.

Sincerely,
Joanna Bennink
Director - WMAAA
jbennink@westmichiganacademy.org

post_text: CORONAVIRUS UPDATE: With the news of the first confirmed cases in Michigan, WMAAA is continuing to monitor the Coronavirus in partnership with Ottawa County Health department, the Ottawa Area ISD, MDHHS, and state government. As always, the health and well-being of our students and staff remain our top priority. We will continue to keep you updated through our website, our facebook page, and through email. This is an evolving situation and we will do our best to keep you informed. If you have questions, please email or call the office.

post_text: Update from Lake Effect Kitchen - We hope you all enjoyed your snow day!
